## Library Book Circulation Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Student/Teacher] --> B[GET /api/library/books]
    B --> C[View Available Books]

    C --> D[Request to Borrow Book]
    D --> E[POST /api/library/issue]

    E --> F[Check: available_copies > 0?]
    F -->|No| G[Show Error: Book Unavailable]
    F -->|Yes| H[Create library_circulation Record]

    H --> I[Set status: issued]
    I --> J[Decrement available_copies]
    J --> K[Increment currently_borrowed]

    K --> L[Set dueDate = today + 14 days]
    L --> M[Return Circulation Record]

    M --> N[Book Issued Successfully]
    N --> O[Book Checkout Complete]

    O --> P[Student Returns Book]
    P --> Q[PATCH /api/library/issue/:id/return]

    Q --> R[Update status: returned]
    R --> S[Set returnDate]
    S --> T[Increment available_copies]
    T --> U[Calculate Fine if Overdue]

    U --> V[Update library_circulation Record]
    V --> W[Return Book Successfully]

    style A fill:#7b68ee
    style H fill:#d4edda
    style M fill:#d4edda
    style R fill:#d4edda
    style V fill:#d4edda
    style W fill:#c3e6cb
```

