## Request-Response Flow (Happy Path)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant UI as Next.js Frontend
    participant API as API Route
    participant Auth as requireAuth()
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    User->>UI: Click "Approve" Button
    UI->>API: POST /api/admin/school-admin-applications/:id/approve

    API->>Auth: requireAuth(['admin'])
    Auth->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE clerkUserId = ?
    DB-->>Auth: User Data
    Auth-->>API: { userId, user }

    API->>Auth: requirePermission(userId, 'schools.approve')
    Auth->>DB: CHECK user_roles
    Auth-->>API: Permission Granted

    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM school_admin_applications WHERE id = ?
    DB-->>API: Application Data

    API->>DB: UPDATE school_admin_applications SET status = 'approved'
    API->>DB: UPDATE users SET type = 'school-admin' WHERE id = ?
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO user_roles (userId, roleId) VALUES (?, ?)

    DB-->>API: Update Complete
    API->>Auth: logger.info("Application approved", { applicationId, userId })

    API-->>UI: { success: true, data: application }
    UI-->>User: Show Success Toast
    UI->>UI: Refresh Page Data
    UI-->>User: Updated List with Approved Badge
```

## Error Handling Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[API Request Received] --> B[try Block]
    B --> C{requireAuth Check}
    C -->|Failed| D[Return 401 Unauthorized]
    C -->|Success| E{requirePermission Check}

    E -->|Failed| F[Return 403 Forbidden]
    E -->|Success| G[Execute Database Query]

    G --> H{Query Successful?}
    H -->|Error| I[logger.apiError]
    H -->|Success| J[logger.info]

    I --> K[Return 500 with Error Message]
    J --> L[Return 200 with Data]

    K --> M[client sees: "An error occurred"]
    L --> N[client receives data]

    style D fill:#f8d7da
    style F fill:#f8d7da
    style I fill:#fff3cd
    style K fill:#f8d7da
    style L fill:#d4edda
    style M fill:#f8d7da
    style N fill:#d4edda
```

